  "text": "Geophis Wagler, 1830 is one of the most diverse genus of snakes in the American continent, with 49 recognized species [CITATION_1] . This genus has a wide distribution range, from northern Mexico, through Central America to northern and western Colombia [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] .",
